                            </tr>

                            <tr style="border:2px solid #000000; background: grey ; color: black; font-weight: bold;">
                                <td>Children (aged 6 to 13)</td>
                                <td>R25 000</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr style="border:2px solid #000000; background: lightgrey; color: black; font-weight: bold;">
                                <td>Children (aged 1 to 5)</td>
                                <td>R15 000</td>

                            <tr style="border:2px solid #000000; background: grey; color: black; font-weight: bold;">
                                <td>Children younger than 1 year</td>
                                <td>R15 000</td>
                            </tr>
                            </tr>
                        </table>

                        <br>
                        <p align="left">
                            If you die, your next of kin or spouse must report your death to your employer’s Human
                            Resources office. When reporting your death your spouse or next of kin should bring along a
                            certified copy of your death certificate and your identity document. This will ensure that
                            theProcess of paying the funeral benefit is done as soon as possible and that the death
                            benefit claim from the Fund is initiated.
                            There are many documents that need to be submitted, the sooner this is done the sooner your
                            benefits can be paid.

                        </p>


                        <p align="left">

                            <strong style="color: red" class="all caps"> Summary of claims process :</strong><br>
                            <li class="bigtfont" ; align="left" style="color:#000000">Complete the claim form<br>
                            <li class="bigtfont" ; align="left" style="color:#000000">Get the employer to sign the claim
                                form<br>
                            <li class="bigtfont" ; align="left" style="color:#000000">Prepare and ensure you have all
                                required, supporting documents<br>
                            <li class="bigtfont" ; align="left" style="color:#000000">Submit the signed claim form with
                                all supporting documents to your HR Office<br><br>
                        </p>
                        <p align="left">

                            <strong style="color: red" class="all caps"> The claims process::</strong><br>
                            <li class="bigtfont" ; align="left" style="color:#000000">All documents are received and
                                verified
                            </li>
